Description: Fragment of oval/flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Button stamp, dotted. Greek inscription. Clay near fine creamy pink.
Curator's comments: Name Polykrates. Probably from same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0922.17. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0651)
